This paper deals with image recognition and deep neural networks, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a de-stylization module that predicts parameters used for scaling and shifting feature maps, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also discusses the generalization of neural networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents a study on how Instagram filters affect image recognition, which could be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
